<subSubSection pageId="29" pageNumber="74" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageId="29" pageNumber="74">
<taxonomicName LSID="257FD852-288F-5F86-A37B-79E5AAA7D6A5" authority="Raf., New Fl. [Rafinesque] 4: 16 (1836)." authorityName="Raf., New Fl. [Rafinesque] 4: 16" authorityYear="1836" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Aizoaceae" genus="Sesuvium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Sesuvium verrucosum" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="29" pageNumber="74" phylum="Spermatophyta" rank="species" species="verrucosum">
<pageBreakToken pageId="29" pageNumber="74" start="start">Sesuvium</pageBreakToken>
verrucosum Raf., New Fl. [Rafinesque] 4: 16 (1836).
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="29" pageNumber="74" type="neotype">
<paragraph pageId="29" pageNumber="74">Neotype</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="29" pageNumber="74">
(
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1600/036364417X694575" author="Bohley, K" journalOrPublisher="Systematic Botany" pageId="32" pageNumber="77" pagination="124 - 147" refId="B9" refString="Bohley, K, Winter, PJD, Kadereit, G, 2017. A revision of Sesuvium (Aizoaceae, Sesuvioideae). Systematic Botany 42 (1): 124 - 147, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1600/036364417X694575" title="A revision of Sesuvium (Aizoaceae, Sesuvioideae)." url="https://doi.org/10.1600/036364417X694575" volume="42" year="2017">Bohley et al. 2017</bibRefCitation>
). [USA] &quot;Salt River&quot;, leg. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="74">Nutt</emphasis>
.[
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="74">all</emphasis>
] (P00680440!); epitype (&quot; 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="74">A.C. Sanders 23186</emphasis>
&quot;, BRIT, n.v.)
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="30" lastPageNumber="75" pageId="29" pageNumber="74" type="nomenclatural notes">
<paragraph pageId="29" pageNumber="74">Nomenclatural notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph lastPageId="30" lastPageNumber="75" pageId="29" pageNumber="74">
It is still doubted whether 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Raf., New Fl. [Rafinesque] 4: 16" authorityYear="1836" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Aizoaceae" genus="Sesuvium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Sesuvium verrucosum" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="29" pageNumber="74" phylum="Spermatophyta" rank="species" species="verrucosum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="74">Sesuvium verrucosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Rafinesque, CS" journalOrPublisher="Plant Systematics and Evolution" pageId="35" pageNumber="80" refId="B64" refString="Rafinesque, CS, 1836. New flora and botany of North America, Part 4. [Printed for the author and publisher], Philadelphia." title="New flora and botany of North America, Part 4. [Printed for the author and publisher], Philadelphia." year="1836">Rafinesque 1836</bibRefCitation>
) is the oldest name for this taxon. Three older names- 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Aizoaceae" genus="Sesuvium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Sesuvium revolutifolium" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="29" pageNumber="74" phylum="Spermatophyta" rank="species" species="revolutifolium">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="74">Sesuvium revolutifolium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Ortega from Cuba (
<bibRefCitation author="Ortega, CG" journalOrPublisher="2, 2 (10). Borntraeger, Berlin" pageId="35" pageNumber="80" refId="B61" refString="Ortega, CG, 1797. Novarum, aut rariorum plantarum horti regii botanici Matritensis descriptionum decades, cum nonnullarum iconibus. Typ. Ibarrriana, Madrid." title="Novarum, aut rariorum plantarum horti regii botanici Matritensis descriptionum decades, cum nonnullarum iconibus. Typ. Ibarrriana, Madrid." year="1797">Ortega 1797</bibRefCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Molluginaceae" genus="S." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. revolutum" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="29" pageNumber="74" phylum="Spermatophyta" rank="species" species="revolutum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="74">S. revolutum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Pers. and 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Molluginaceae" genus="S." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. sessile" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="29" pageNumber="74" phylum="Spermatophyta" rank="species" species="sessile">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="74">S. sessile</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Pers. (
<bibRefCitation author="Persoon, CH" journalOrPublisher="Plant Systematics and Evolution" pageId="35" pageNumber="80" refId="B63" refString="Persoon, CH, 1806. Synopsis Plantarum: seu Enchiridium botanicum, complectens enumerationem systematicam specierum hucusque cognitarum, Vol. 2, part 1. Cramer, Paris." title="Synopsis Plantarum: seu Enchiridium botanicum, complectens enumerationem systematicam specierum hucusque cognitarum, Vol. 2, part 1. Cramer, Paris." year="1806">Persoon 1806</bibRefCitation>
), both of unknown origin-may be conspecific with 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Molluginaceae" genus="S." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. verrucosum" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="29" pageNumber="74" phylum="Spermatophyta" rank="species" species="verrucosum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="74">S. verrucosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, the 
<pageBreakToken pageId="30" pageNumber="75" start="start">description</pageBreakToken>
of both 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Molluginaceae" genus="S." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. revolutum" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="30" pageNumber="75" phylum="Spermatophyta" rank="species" species="revolutum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="75">S. revolutum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Molluginaceae" genus="S." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. sessile" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="30" pageNumber="75" phylum="Spermatophyta" rank="species" species="sessile">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="75">S. sessile</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is very short and poor and no original material could be traced. The protologue of 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Molluginaceae" genus="S." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. revolutifolium" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="30" pageNumber="75" phylum="Spermatophyta" rank="species" species="revolutifolium">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="75">S. revolutifolium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
completely matches the habit of 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Molluginaceae" genus="S." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. verrucosum" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="30" pageNumber="75" phylum="Spermatophyta" rank="species" species="verrucosum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="75">S. verrucosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but it is not sure whether the plants from North America are identical to those from Cuba. 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Aizoaceae" genus="Sesuvium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Sesuvium revolutifolium" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="30" pageNumber="75" phylum="Spermatophyta" rank="species" species="revolutifolium">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="75">Sesuvium revolutifolium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Molluginaceae" genus="S." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. sessile" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="30" pageNumber="75" phylum="Spermatophyta" rank="species" species="sessile">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="75">S. sessile</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Molluginaceae" genus="S." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. revolutum" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="30" pageNumber="75" phylum="Spermatophyta" rank="species" species="revolutum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="75">S. revolutum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have been synonymised with 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Molluginaceae" genus="S." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. portulacastrum" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="30" pageNumber="75" phylum="Spermatophyta" rank="species" species="portulacastrum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="75">S. portulacastrum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1600/036364417X694575" author="Bohley, K" journalOrPublisher="Systematic Botany" pageId="32" pageNumber="77" pagination="124 - 147" refId="B9" refString="Bohley, K, Winter, PJD, Kadereit, G, 2017. A revision of Sesuvium (Aizoaceae, Sesuvioideae). Systematic Botany 42 (1): 124 - 147, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1600/036364417X694575" title="A revision of Sesuvium (Aizoaceae, Sesuvioideae)." url="https://doi.org/10.1600/036364417X694575" volume="42" year="2017">Bohley et al. (2017)</bibRefCitation>
, but the nomenclature of all three species needs further study.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="30" pageNumber="75" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="30" pageNumber="75">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="30" pageNumber="75">
The most indicative characters of this species are: 1) perennial life history, 2) presence of abundant papillae on stems and leaves, 3) 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Aizoaceae" genus="Sesuvium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Sesuvium sessile" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="30" pageNumber="75" phylum="Spermatophyta" rank="species" species="sessile">Sesuvium sessile</taxonomicName>
turbinate flower buds and capsules and 4) clearly expressed detachments of the aril from the seed coat. Usually, the stems are rooting; however 
<bibRefCitation author="Ferren, WR" journalOrPublisher="4. Oxford University Press, New York, Oxford" pageId="33" pageNumber="78" pagination="80 - 81" refId="B20" refString="Ferren, WR, 2003. Sesuvium. In: Flora of North America, North of Mexico, Vol. 4. Oxford University Press, New York, Oxford: 80 - 81" title="Sesuvium." volumeTitle="Flora of North America, North of Mexico, Vol." year="2003">Ferren (2003)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Baldwin, BG" journalOrPublisher="ZooKeys" pageId="32" pageNumber="77" refId="B6" refString="Baldwin, BG, Goldman, DH, Keil, DJ, Patterson, R, Rosatti, TJ, Wilken, DH, 2012. The Jepson Manual: Vascular plants of California. University of California Press, Berkeley, Lon Angeles, London." title="The Jepson Manual: Vascular plants of California. University of California Press, Berkeley, Lon Angeles, London." year="2012">Baldwin et al. (2012)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Molluginaceae" genus="S." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. verrucosum" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="30" pageNumber="75" phylum="Spermatophyta" rank="species" species="verrucosum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="75">S. verrucosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a non-rooting plant (probably applicable to younger plants, as observed in the specimen from Cape Verde listed below). For detailed morphological description, see 
<bibRefCitation author="Fadaie, F" journalOrPublisher="Iranian Journal of Botany" pageId="33" pageNumber="78" pagination="87 - 88" refId="B19" refString="Fadaie, F, Attar, F, Ghahreman, A, 2006. A new record of Aizoaceae (Sesuvium verrucosum Raf.) for the flora of Iran. Iranian Journal of Botany 12 (1): 87 - 88" title="A new record of Aizoaceae (Sesuvium verrucosum Raf.) for the flora of Iran." volume="12" year="2006">Fadaie et al. (2006)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1600/036364417X694575" author="Bohley, K" journalOrPublisher="Systematic Botany" pageId="32" pageNumber="77" pagination="124 - 147" refId="B9" refString="Bohley, K, Winter, PJD, Kadereit, G, 2017. A revision of Sesuvium (Aizoaceae, Sesuvioideae). Systematic Botany 42 (1): 124 - 147, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1600/036364417X694575" title="A revision of Sesuvium (Aizoaceae, Sesuvioideae)." url="https://doi.org/10.1600/036364417X694575" volume="42" year="2017">Bohley et al. (2017)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
